 AC/DC drummer Phil Rudd pleaded guilty in a New Zealand court , to charges of threatening to kill and of possessing drugs .
Rudd , 60 , was charged with two counts of threatening and possession of methamphetamine and of cannabis , which stem from a police raid on his waterfront North Island mansion on November 6 .
The veteran rocker had originally pleaded not guilty to the charges .
He changed his plea to guilty on Tuesday .